{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/background-information/causes/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"add551e4-2d3b-5eca-b185-62b80e4e7446","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 284796ec-1b03-4cee-a3d6-8801c41215ec --><h2>What causes it?</h2><!-- end field 284796ec-1b03-4cee-a3d6-8801c41215ec -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item b5908701-82f3-4937-8bcf-f5a673e1117c --><!-- begin field 2741bb0c-18ab-4eec-9104-74666f794e57 --><ul><li><strong>Fatigue symptoms can be a non-specific indicator of underlying physiological or physical pathology, psychosocial distress, or a combination of causesÂ </strong>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/references/\">Nicholson, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/references/\">Stadje, 2016</a>]<strong>.</strong><ul><li>Physiological causes include pregnancy, breastfeeding, inadequate rest or sleep, and excessive exercise.</li><li>Physical causes include anaemia, diabetes mellitus, glandular fever, or malignancy.</li><li>Psychological or psychosocial causes include depression, anxiety, loss, and stress.<ul><li>A Dutch prospective primary care study of 93,297 patient-years that explored four common physical symptom presentations, found a physical or psychological cause was identified in two-thirds of cases of fatigue, but in one-third of cases no specific cause was found [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/references/\">Okkes, 2002</a>].</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><strong>The exact aetiology and pathophysiology of chronic fatigue syndrome is unknown </strong>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/references/\">Collin, 2017</a>]<strong>.</strong><ul><li>Expert opinion in a review article notes that it is typically accompanied by multiple other symptoms suggesting a combination of inflammatory, immune, viral, and endocrine dysfunction [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/references/\">Bansal, 2016</a>].</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 2741bb0c-18ab-4eec-9104-74666f794e57 --><!-- end item b5908701-82f3-4937-8bcf-f5a673e1117c -->","topic":{"id":"61f35df8-36d2-541e-b997-0b78bad96289","topicId":"21fb5f0f-1e06-43c8-990f-bcded8cfc676","topicName":"Tiredness/fatigue in adults","slug":"tiredness-fatigue-in-adults","lastRevised":"Last revised in March 2020","chapters":[{"id":"404cb5e0-c0b1-516d-b548-9486e82f51b3","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"defb4b1a-b1c0-5607-98c7-67099c37b768","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"630ed210-1441-537d-a2e4-80c614c19753","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"4af39332-0dc0-5737-9443-75ab1ccb7e46","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"499e2dc9-675d-5c9c-8e90-33be13310544","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"6d9550cf-4496-5399-9386-2221acab329e","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"124b7023-365f-54a7-a251-a963db2de643","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"fdfc586d-81b1-5d44-a036-a438634061a5","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"56625d11-efe9-5e3f-b417-bc52a5fd8647","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"709f0c15-0a45-522f-ad1f-264575775c32","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"bbcffc23-5ef8-55a0-a824-0e0d22076edb","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"7fe1e226-6357-5456-a7f9-c486054d1